      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BELTONE BOY (1) has been in the frame at his last two runs, most recently when third (15.99) in a Grade 3/4 over 272m at The Gardens. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Can make amends this time. SAIL AWAY SAM (8) was last seen getting around 400m at The Gardens in a swift 22.86 for a one length win. Expecting another bold showing. SILENT MINUTE (2) was never in contention last time after settling off pace at Richmond, but prior to that won by one length at this track (22.46) beating Pitman Go Well in a Grade 5 on April 14. Has the ability to give this a shake. LOCHINVAR GRACE (3) will make her presence felt following a brief layoff.",
